is_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Price-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Price_12-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://ocw.mit.edu/ans7870/resources/price/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://ocw.mit.edu/ans7870/resources/price/index.htm" rel="nofollow">MIT essays</a> by James F. Price, Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution (2006). See in particular §4.3 in the <a href="http://ocw.mit.edu/ans7870/resources/price/essay2.pdf" class="external text" title="http://ocw.mit.edu/ans7870/resources/price/essay2.pdf" rel="nofollow">Coriolis lecture</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Taylor0-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Taylor0_13-0" title="">^</a></b> The claim is made that in the Falklands in WW I, the British failed to correct their sights for the southern hemisphere, and so missed their targets. <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJohn_Robert_Taylor2005">John Robert Taylor (2005). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=P1kCtNr-pJsC&amp;pg=PA364" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=P1kCtNr-pJsC&amp;pg=PA364" rel="nofollow">Classical Mechanics</a></i>. University Science Books. p.&#160;364; Problem 9.28. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/189138922X" class="internal">ISBN 189138922X</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=P1kCtNr-pJsC&amp;pg=PA364" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=P1kCtNr-pJsC&amp;pg=PA364" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=P1kCtNr-pJsC&amp;pg=PA364</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Classical+Mechanics&amp;rft.aulast=John+Robert+Taylor&amp;rft.au=John+Robert+Taylor&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B364%3B+Problem+9.28&amp;rft.pub=University+Science+Books&amp;rft.isbn=189138922X&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DP1kCtNr-pJsC%26pg%3DPA364&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coriolis_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>. For set up of the calculations, see <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFDonald_E._Carlucci.2C_Sidney_S._Jacobson2007">Donald E. Carlucci, Sidney S. Jacobson (2007). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=pX9Tzs7VuSoC&amp;pg=PA225" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=pX9Tzs7VuSoC&amp;pg=PA225" rel="nofollow">Ballistics</a></i>. CRC Press. p.&#160;225. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1420066188" class="internal">ISBN 1420066188</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=pX9Tzs7VuSoC&amp;pg=PA225" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=pX9Tzs7VuSoC&amp;pg=PA225" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=pX9Tzs7VuSoC&amp;pg=PA225</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ballistics&amp;rft.aulast=Donald+E.+Carlucci%2C+Sidney+S.+Jacobson&amp;rft.au=Donald+E.+Carlucci%2C+Sidney+S.+Jacobson&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B225&amp;rft.pub=CRC+Press&amp;rft.isbn=1420066188&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DpX9Tzs7VuSoC%26pg%3DPA225&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coriolis_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-caution-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-caution_14-0" title="">^</a></b> Here the description "radially inward" means "toward the axis of rotation". That direction is <i>not</i> toward the <a href="/wiki/Osculating_circle" title="Osculating circle">center of curvature</a> of the path, however, which is the direction of the true centripetal force. Hence, the quotation marks on "centripetal".</li>
<li id="cite_note-Owen-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Owen_15-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGeorge_E._Owen2003">George E. Owen (2003). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=9dRxGCktg7QC&amp;pg=PA22&amp;dq=Coriolis+carousel&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=a2n5yMAC_3u7QCrcldHIrb2R_1U#PPA23,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=9dRxGCktg7QC&amp;pg=PA22&amp;dq=Coriolis+carousel&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=a2n5yMAC_3u7QCrcldHIrb2R_1U#PPA23,M1" rel="nofollow">Fundamentals of Scientific Mathematics</a></i> (original edition published by Harper &amp; Row, New York, 1964 ed.). Courier Dover Publications. p.&#160;p.23. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486428087" class="internal">ISBN 0486428087</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=9dRxGCktg7QC&amp;pg=PA22&amp;dq=Coriolis+carousel&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=a2n5yMAC_3u7QCrcldHIrb2R_1U#PPA23,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=9dRxGCktg7QC&amp;pg=PA22&amp;dq=Coriolis+carousel&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=a2n5yMAC_3u7QCrcldHIrb2R_1U#PPA23,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=9dRxGCktg7QC&amp;pg=PA22&amp;dq=Coriolis+carousel&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=a2n5yMAC_3u7QCrcldHIrb2R_1U#PPA23,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fundamentals+of+Scientific+Mathematics&amp;rft.aulast=George+E.+Owen&amp;rft.au=George+E.+Owen&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3Bp.23&amp;rft.edition=original+edition+published+by+Harper+%26+Row%2C+New+York%2C+1964&amp;rft.pub=Courier+Dover+Publications&amp;rft.isbn=0486428087&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D9dRxGCktg7QC%26pg%3DPA22%26dq%3DCoriolis%2Bcarousel%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D0%26sig%3Da2n5yMAC_3u7QCrcldHIrb2R_1U%23PPA23%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coriolis_effect"><span style="display: non