<li id="cite_note-McCully2-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-McCully2_18-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJames_Greig_McCully2006">James Greig McCully (2006). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=RijQELAGnEIC&amp;pg=PA76&amp;dq=airplane+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=zew-P2KGA8-NMxFn0Sn23zI_x2Y#PPA75,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=RijQELAGnEIC&amp;pg=PA76&amp;dq=airplane+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=zew-P2KGA8-NMxFn0Sn23zI_x2Y#PPA75,M1" rel="nofollow">Beyond the moon: A Conversational, Common Sense Guide to Understanding the Tides</a></i>. World Scientific. p.&#160;74–76. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9812566430" class="internal">ISBN 9812566430</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=RijQELAGnEIC&amp;pg=PA76&amp;dq=airplane+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=zew-P2KGA8-NMxFn0Sn23zI_x2Y#PPA75,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=RijQELAGnEIC&amp;pg=PA76&amp;dq=airplane+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=zew-P2KGA8-NMxFn0Sn23zI_x2Y#PPA75,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=RijQELAGnEIC&amp;pg=PA76&amp;dq=airplane+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=zew-P2KGA8-NMxFn0Sn23zI_x2Y#PPA75,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Beyond+the+moon%3A+A+Conversational%2C+Common+Sense+Guide+to+Understanding+the+Tides&amp;rft.aulast=James+Greig+McCully&amp;rft.au=James+Greig+McCully&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B74%E2%80%9376&amp;rft.pub=World+Scientific&amp;rft.isbn=9812566430&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DRijQELAGnEIC%26pg%3DPA76%26dq%3Dairplane%2BCoriolis%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D0%26sig%3Dzew-P2KGA8-NMxFn0Sn23zI_x2Y%23PPA75%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coriolis_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Ginsberg-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Ginsberg_19-0" title="">^</a></b> For the set-up of this problem, see <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJerry_H._Ginsberg2007">Jerry H. Ginsberg (2007). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=Y1x399JntpkC&amp;pg=PA151&amp;dq=catch+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=DMDBWoN19LaaKQWi70BNjKnlgIE#PPA152,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=Y1x399JntpkC&amp;pg=PA151&amp;dq=catch+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=DMDBWoN19LaaKQWi70BNjKnlgIE#PPA152,M1" rel="nofollow">Engineering Dynamics</a></i>. Cambridge University Press. p.&#160;p. 152. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521883032" class="internal">ISBN 0521883032</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=Y1x399JntpkC&amp;pg=PA151&amp;dq=catch+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=DMDBWoN19LaaKQWi70BNjKnlgIE#PPA152,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=Y1x399JntpkC&amp;pg=PA151&amp;dq=catch+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=DMDBWoN19LaaKQWi70BNjKnlgIE#PPA152,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=Y1x399JntpkC&amp;pg=PA151&amp;dq=catch+Coriolis&amp;lr=&amp;as_brr=0&amp;sig=DMDBWoN19LaaKQWi70BNjKnlgIE#PPA152,M1</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Engineering+Dynamics&amp;rft.aulast=Jerry+H.+Ginsberg&amp;rft.au=Jerry+H.+Ginsberg&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3Bp.+152&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0521883032&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DY1x399JntpkC%26pg%3DPA151%26dq%3Dcatch%2BCoriolis%26lr%3D%26as_brr%3D0%26sig%3DDMDBWoN19LaaKQWi70BNjKnlgIE%23PPA152%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Coriolis_effect"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-parabola-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-parabola_20-0" title="">^</a></b> When a container of fluid is rotating on a turntable, the surface of the fluid naturally assumes the correct <a href="/wiki/Parabola" title="Parabola">parabolic</a> shape. This fact may be exploited to make a parabolic turntable by using a fluid that sets after several hours, such as a synthetic <a href="/wiki/Resin" title="Resin">resin</a>. For a video of the Coriolis effect on such a parabolic surface, see <a href="http://www-paoc.mit.edu/labweb/lab5/gfd_v.htm" class="external text" title="http://www-paoc.mit.edu/labweb/lab5/gfd_v.htm" rel="nofollow">Geophysical fluid dynamics lab demonstration</a> John Marshall, Massachusetts Institute of Technology.</li>
<li id="cite_note-animation-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-animation_21-0" title="">^</a></b> For a java applet of the Coriolis effect on such a parabolic surface, see <a href="http://mensch.org/physlets/inosc.html" class="external text" title="http://mensch.org/physlets/inosc.html" rel="nofollow">Brian Fiedler</a> School of Meteorology at the University of Oklahoma.</li>
