<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.ems.psu.edu/~fraser/Bad/BadCoriolis.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ems.psu.edu/~fraser/Bad/BadCoriolis.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Bad Coriolis.</i></a> An article uncovering misinformation about the Coriolis effect. By Alistair B. Fraser, Emeritus Professor of Meteorology at <a href="/wiki/Pennsylvania_State_University" title="Pennsylvania State University">Pennsylvania State University</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.physics.ohio-state.edu/~dvandom/Edu/newcor.html" class="external text" title="http://www.physics.ohio-state.edu/~dvandom/Edu/newcor.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Getting Around The Coriolis Force</i></a>, an intuitive explanation</li>
<li><a href="http://www.classzone.com/books/earth_science/terc/content/visualizations/es1904/es1904page01.cfm?chapter_no=visualization" class="external text" title="http://www.classzone.com/books/earth_science/terc/content/visualizations/es1904/es1904page01.cfm?chapter_no=visualization" rel="nofollow">Observe an animation of the Coriolis effect over Earth's surface</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=49JwbrXcPjc" class="external text" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=49JwbrXcPjc" rel="nofollow">Animation clip</a> showing scenes as viewed from both an inertial frame and a rotating frame of reference, visualizing the Coriolis and centrifugal forces.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.inwit.com/inwit/writings/coriolisforce.html" class="external text" title="http://www.inwit.com/inwit/writings/coriolisforce.html" rel="nofollow">Vincent Mallette <i>The Coriolis Force</i> @ INWIT</a></li>
